<item>
            <title>[LU-12763] Use alternate ping processing for non-mr peers</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12763</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Router peers without multi-rail capabilities (i.e. older Lustre&lt;br/&gt;
versions) or router peers that have discovery disabled need to use&lt;br/&gt;
the alternate ping processing introduced by &lt;a href=&quot;https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-12422&quot; title=&quot;LNet MR routing: update route state in case discovery is off&quot; class=&quot;issue-link&quot; data-issue-key=&quot;LU-12422&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;LU-12422&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;. Otherwise,&lt;br/&gt;
these peers go through the normal discovery processing, but their&lt;br/&gt;
remote network interfaces are never added to the peer object. This&lt;br/&gt;
causes routes through these peers to be considered down when&lt;br/&gt;
avoid_asym_router_failure is enabled.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
